        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: isolate plugin test helpers from sdk exports",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Remove Vitest-backed Plugin SDK test-helper subpaths from public `openclaw` package exports and add `packages/plugin-test-kit` as the private workspace boundary for OpenClaw repo test contracts and fixtures.\n- Move repo tests to `@openclaw/plugin-test-kit/*`, keeping runner-neutral contracts and fixtures separate from the Vitest adapter and keeping provider HTTP `vi.mock` helpers on explicit `@openclaw/plugin-test-kit/provider-http-mocks`.\n- Add release/package guardrails for Vitest leakage in `dist/plugin-sdk`, update compatibility/docs to stop recommending removed public test-helper subpaths, and move browser test support under `extensions/browser/src/test-support`.\n\nCrabbox/Kova context: clean beta package validation failed with `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND Cannot find package 'vitest'` when importing public Plugin SDK test-contract subpaths from `openclaw@beta`. This PR removes that dev-only dependency path from the public package surface.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.test.src.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/test-src-vitest-dep.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test-vitest-dep.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.test.ui.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/test-ui-vitest-dep.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-vitest-dep.tsbuildinfo`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-subpaths.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-package-contract-guardrails.test.ts src/plugins/compat/registry.test.ts test/release-check.test.ts test/vitest-scoped-config.test.ts test/vitest-extensions-config.test.ts ui/src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/extension-package-project-boundaries.test.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/control-auth.test.ts extensions/browser/src/cli/browser-cli-inspect.test.ts extensions/browser/src/browser/routes/tabs.attach-only.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/alibaba/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/byteplus/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/deepinfra/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/google/speech-provider.test.ts extensions/openai/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/qwen/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/runway/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/together/video-generation-provider.test.ts extensions/xai/video-generation-provider.test.ts`\n- `pnpm --dir ui test src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts --run`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/compat/registry.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-subpaths.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-package-contract-guardrails.test.ts test/release-check.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/contracts/extension-package-project-boundaries.test.ts test/vitest-scoped-config.test.ts test/vitest-extensions-config.test.ts test/release-check.test.ts ui/src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/vitest-scoped-config.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-package-contract-guardrails.test.ts`\n- Static built dist scan via `collectPluginSdkVitestImportErrors`: `plugin-sdk vitest import check passed`\n- Built package export import smoke: `imported 303 plugin SDK package exports`\n- Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox `tbx_01kskmps28kp92pq97z2a4ww89`, Actions run `26487368309`: `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, `pnpm build`, static `dist/plugin-sdk` Vitest scan, `npm pack --ignore-scripts`, clean `npm install <tarball> --omit=dev --ignore-scripts`, assert clean consumer cannot resolve `vitest`, and import every `openclaw/plugin-sdk*` package export. Result: `remote clean install imported 303 plugin SDK exports without vitest`.\n- `git diff --check --cached`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --prompt \"Final review after narrowing runner-neutral declaration shims.\"`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings reported\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: public Plugin SDK test-contract/package exports could require the dev-only `vitest` dependency from a clean installed `openclaw@beta` package.\nReal environment tested: local source checkout after patch, plus Blacksmith Testbox through Crabbox clean package install proof on `tbx_01kskmps28kp92pq97z2a4ww89`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: local commands listed in Verification; remote proof ran `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, `pnpm build`, static `dist/plugin-sdk` Vitest scan, `npm pack --ignore-scripts`, clean `npm install <tarball> --omit=dev --ignore-scripts`, an assertion that the clean consumer cannot resolve `vitest`, and import smoke for every installed `openclaw/plugin-sdk*` package export.\nEvidence after fix: local `pnpm build` passed; local and remote static dist scans reported no Vitest imports in built `dist/plugin-sdk` exports; local built package export smoke imported 303 SDK exports; Testbox clean install imported 303 SDK exports without Vitest; focused tests/type gates passed; autoreview reported no actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: public Plugin SDK package exports no longer include the retired Vitest-backed test-helper subpaths, the built plugin SDK export set imports without requiring Vitest, and a clean consumer package install does not declare or resolve `vitest` while importing every remaining Plugin SDK export.\nWhat was not tested: the full named Kova/Clawditor/Crabpot release lanes were not rerun in this session. The Testbox clean package proof covers the reported missing-`vitest` package-boundary failure directly. Broad extension package-boundary compile was attempted earlier and then blocked by unrelated `extensions/memory-lancedb/index.ts` missing `@lancedb/lancedb` types after the browser private-test-kit boundary issue was fixed.\n",
